flowent

Class Flowent

  • java.lang.Object
    • flowent.Flowent

  • public class Flowent
extends java.lang.Object
    Flowent is a fluent interface API written for the Java Programming Language. Flowent is a project by CodeDojo, developed by many different CodeDojo developers. From a user's perspective, it looks nice and simple, while the API does all of the work for you. If you need help, visit Flowent API Help on Blogger.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Adrian Gjerstad

      • runMethod

        public Flowent runMethod(FlowentFunction ff)
        Runs the execute method in the FlowentFunction passed in. If the method execution has any uncaught exceptions, the onError method will be called. No arguments may be passed in.
        Parameters:
        ff - The FlowentFunction method to be run.
        Returns:
        This Flowent object for method chaining purposes.
        See Also:
        FlowentFunction, FlowentFunction.execute(Flowent), FlowentFunction.onError(Flowent, Exception, String)

        public void exit(java.lang.String message)

        Parameters:
